      "body": {
        "storage": {
          "value": "<div class=\"panel conf-macro output-block\" style=\"border-style: solid;border-width: 1px;\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-name=\"panel\"><div class=\"panelHeader\" style=\"border-bottom-width: 1px;border-bottom-style: solid;\"><b>On This Page</b></div><div class=\"panelContent\">\n<p> </p><div class=\"toc-macro client-side-toc-macro  conf-macro output-block\" data-csslistindent=\"3\" data-headerelements=\"H1,H2,H3,H4,H5,H6,H7\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-macro-name=\"toc\"> </div><p> </p>\n</div></div><p> </p><p>A code formatter for the Eclipse IDE that can be used across all DDF projects will allow developers to format code similarly and minimize merge issues in the future.</p><p>DDF uses an updated version of the Apache ServiceMix Code Formatter (<a href=\"http://servicemix.apache.org/developers/building.html\" class=\"external-link\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://servicemix.apache.org/developers/building.html</a>) for code formatting. </p><h1 id=\"FormattingSourceCode-LoadtheCodeFormatterIntotheEclipseIDE\">Load the Code Formatter Into the Eclipse IDE</h1><p><em><strong>DOWNLOAD THIS FILE</strong></em>: <a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/codice/ddf-support/master/support-checkstyle/src/main/resources/ddf-eclipse-code-formatter.xml\" class=\"external-link\" rel=\"nofollow\">ddf-eclipse-code-formatter.xml</a> (NOTE: <strong>Right-Click</strong> the link and <span style=\"line-height: 1.4285715;\">Select </span><strong style=\"line-height: 1.4285715;\">Save Link As </strong>if the browser opens the file in another window).</p><ol><li><p>In Eclipse, select <strong>Window → Preferences</strong>. The Preferences window opens.</p></li><li><p>Select <strong>Java → Code Style → Formatter</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Select the <strong>Edit...</strong> button and load the attached <a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/codice/ddf-support/master/support-checkstyle/src/main/resources/ddf-eclipse-code-formatter.xml\" class=\"external-link\" rel=\"nofollow\">ddf-eclipse-code-formatter.xml</a>.</p></li><li><p>Select the <strong>OK</strong> button.</p><p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" src=\"/wiki/download/attachments/1179681/eclipse-import-formatter.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1434506565659&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"/wiki/download/attachments/1179681/eclipse-import-formatter.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1434506565659&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1182958\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"eclipse-import-formatter.png\" data-base-url=\"https://codice.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"1179681\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"19\"></span></p></li></ol><h1 id=\"FormattingSourceCode-LoadtheCodeFormatterIntoIntelliJIDEA\">Load the Code Formatter Into IntelliJ IDEA</h1><p><em><strong>DOWNLOAD THIS FILE</strong></em>: <a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/codice/ddf-support/master/support-checkstyle/src/main/resources/ddf-intellij-code-formatter.jar\" class=\"external-link\" rel=\"nofollow\">ddf-intellij-code-formatter.jar</a> (NOTE: <strong>Right-Click</strong> the link and <span>Select </span><strong>Save Link As </strong>if the browser opens the file in another window).</p><p>Previously, in IntelliJ, we would just import the Eclipse settings. However, now there is a IntelliJ settings jar that will import the code styles.</p><ol><li><span style=\"line-height: 1.4285715;\">Open</span><strong style=\"line-height: 1.4285715;\"> IntelliJ</strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.4285715;\"> IDEA.</span></li><li>Select<strong> File → Import Settings</strong>. The file selection window opens.</li><li>Choose <a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/codice/ddf-support/master/support-checkstyle/src/main/resources/ddf-intellij-code-formatter.jar\" class=\"external-link\" rel=\"nofollow\">ddf-intellij-code-formatter.jar</a>.</li><li>Select OK. NOTE: this will restart IntelliJ.<br/><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" src=\"/wiki/download/attachments/1179681/intellij-import-formatter.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1434506911271&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"/wiki/download/attachments/1179681/intellij-import-formatter.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1434506911271&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1182960\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"intellij-import-formatter.png\" data-base-url=\"https://codice.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"1179681\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"19\"></span></li></ol><h1 id=\"FormattingSourceCode-FormatYourSourceCodeUsingEclipse\">Format Your Source Code Using Eclipse </h1><p>A developer may write code and format it before saving.</p><ol><li>Before the file is saved, highlight all of the source code in the IDE editor window.</li><li>Right-click on the highlighted code.</li><li>Select <strong>Source → Format. </strong>The code formatter is applied to the source code and the file can be saved. </li></ol><h1 id=\"FormattingSourceCode-SetUpSaveActionsinEclipse\">Set Up Save Actions in Eclipse</h1><p>A developer can also set up Save Actions to format the source code automatically.</p><ol><li>Open Eclipse.</li><li><p>Select <strong>Window → Preferences</strong> (<strong>Eclipse → Preferences</strong> on Mac). The Preferences window opens.</p></li><li><p>Select <strong>Java → Editor → Save Actions</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Select <strong>Perform the selected actions on save</strong>.</p></li><li>Select <strong>Format source code</strong>.</li><li>Select <strong>Format all lines </strong>or <strong>Format edited lines</strong>, as necessary. </li><li>Optionally, select <strong>Organize imports</strong> (recommended).</li><li>Select the <strong>Apply </strong>button.</li><li>Select the <strong>OK </strong>button.<br/><br/><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" src=\"/wiki/download/attachments/1179681/eclipse-save-action.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1434507346259&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"/wiki/download/attachments/1179681/eclipse-save-action.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1434507346259&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1182959\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"eclipse-save-action.png\" data-base-url=\"https://codice.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"1179681\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"19\"></span></li></ol><h1 id=\"FormattingSourceCode-FormatSourceCodeUsingIntelliJ\">Format Source Code Using IntelliJ</h1><p>In the toolbar, select <strong>Code → Reformat Code </strong>or use the keyboard shortcut Ctrl-Alt-L.</p><p> </p>",
